Hill:
Intermittent social runners
Benefit from targeted internal data and external data
In order to assess and enhance race performance in an engaging manner.

SubHill:
RAM platform will also give suggestions based on the data analytics and runner preferences, about training programs and other ways to prepare better and perform better in future races.

Story:
As an intermittent social runner
I want to know about RAM races that match my personalized data
So that I participate in the right races in order to enjoy more and/or improve my performance

Acceptance Criteria 1:
Given I'm an intermittent social runner with a RAM account
When I log onto RAM website or app
Then I will see a recommended races section that has personalized race recommendations that I will likely be interested in

Acceptance Criteria 2:
Given I'm an intermittent social runner who is turning/have turned 50 within the current calendar year
When I log onto RAM website or app and go to recommended races section
Then I will see a race that is only for people who are turning 50 in the current year to celebrate turning 50 and still staying fit

Acceptance Criteria 3:
Given I'm an intermittent social runner whose last race finish time was within 10% longer than benchmark (benchmark: 20 min for 5k, 40 for 10k, 1hr for 15k, 4hr for full marathon / 10% longer: 20~22min for 5k etc)
When I log onto RAM website or app and go to recommended races section
Then I will see a race that is only for people who were in the same performance group that is motivating them/me to aim for finishing within the benchmark
